      <p>Travel brewing is where good intentions usually go to die. You are tired, the hotel kettle is questionable, and your grinder clicks feel like guesses. That is why the best travel ratio is not some flashy concentrate trick. It is a simple 1:15 recipe that still tastes good when your setup is less than perfect.</p>
      <p>The AeroPress Go pairs well with that approach because the whole thing stays compact and predictable. Use 14 grams of coffee, 210 grams of water, and keep the grind in a forgiving medium-fine band. You get a cup that tastes lively and clear, even when you are brewing in a cabin, an office kitchen, or a weird Airbnb with one decent mug and no counter space.</p>
